I have made this recipe many times with great results, the original is great but here are my tips. One warning: This doesn't make muffins as sweet as the store-bought ones (which in my opinion, is a good thing). I normally double the recipe and, as I rarely have buttermilk on hand, have used plain or vanilla yogurt or a mixture with sour cream instead to soak the oats. I normally add more spices to suit my taste, a teaspoon or more of cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, etc. and have included chopped nuts and craisins (my favorite) instead of currants. To keep your fruit moist, pour hot water or put them in a pyrex measuring cup with hot water in the microwave for a minute or two, let them steep for a few minutes, then drain and add them to the mixture. You will never have that dried out, burned tasting fruit in a muffin (or cookie - use the tip whenever using dried fruit like raisins) again. Yum!

