Good stuff. Unlike all the lowfat reviewers, I kept all the fat intact. The texture and moisture were right on. I, too, think that the buttermilk is key. (In fact, that is partially why I chose this recipe, and also the butter which adds more flavor than oil does as is called for in many muffin recipes). Next time I will keep the basic recipe as is and add a few things to enhance the flavor: zest of one lemon or orange, one tsp. vanilla, a little cinnamon and nutmeg, and a bit of turbinado sugar on top before baking. I also soaked the buttermilk and oats in the fridge overnight to save time in the morning. Great shortcut. Try them, a dee-lish oatmeal muffin recipe. I would give them four stars except it is a muffin recipe, not brownies or chili or the like!

