Rating: 3
I really liked these muffins, and have made them twice. The first time, I made the muffins for my neighbors--exactly as written. (Except to sprinkle on some turbinado sugar on the tops before baking.) The second time, I modified the recipe to make it healthier. I blended the 1 c. oats in the blender a bit, and substituted soymilk with 1 TBS. lemon juice mixed in. (Instead of the buttermilk.) In place of the beaten egg, I used 2 TBS. of apple juice. The 1/2 c. melted butter was replaced with 1 very ripe mashed banana, and the 1 c. AP flour was replaced with whole wheat *PASTRY* flour. In addition to the above changes, I also left the currants out. Added vanilla, cinnamon, cloves, & allspice. Sprinkled turbinado sugar on the tops of the muffins the second time around as well. The turbinado sugar (aka: Sugar In The Raw) adds a wonderful crunch. Healthy, and not too sweet. Yumm. :o)

